               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1464" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1464" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1464" type="surname" value="JOLLIFFE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1464" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS JOLLIFFE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to John Wells, pawnbroker, Adam's-row, Hampstead-road. On the 9th of April I saw the prisoner, and ano<lb></lb>ther, in front of the shop—in consequence of something a woman told me, I went after them, and came up to them in Adam's-row—they were still together I saw the person the prisoner was with, give him this mortise-gauge—I fol<lb></lb>lowed the prisoner—he ran—when I was close behind him, he threw the gauge under a cart—a sweep picked it up, and gave it me—I caught him in Crescent-street, Euston-square—he said, "Pray, forgive me this once"—he</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080222"></xptr>
               <p>was taken to the station—this is Mr. Wells's property—it was placed on a tray in front of the shop—my attention was drawn off by another party, and that enabled a person to take it.</p>
